{"metadata":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"DriveRef","kind":"identifier"}],"roleHeading":"Structure","modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"title":"DriveRef","externalID":"s:3GIO8DriveRefV","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"DriveRef"}],"symbolKind":"struct"},"topicSections":[{"anchor":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DriveRef\/init(_:)-41xx","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DriveRef\/init(_:)-55g5o","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DriveRef\/init(_:)-59lbv","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DriveRef\/init(_:)-5q9y1","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DriveRef\/init(_:)-p3ca","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DriveRef\/init(cPointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DriveRef\/init(constPointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DriveRef\/init(gconstpointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DriveRef\/init(gpointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DriveRef\/init(mutating:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DriveRef\/init(opaquePointer:)"],"generated":true,"title":"Initializers"},{"generated":true,"title":"Instance Properties","anchor":"Instance-Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DriveRef\/ptr"]},{"anchor":"Default-Implementations","generated":true,"title":"Default Implementations","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DriveRef\/DriveProtocol-Implementations","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DriveRef\/PointerWrapper-Implementations"]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/driveref"]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DriveRef"},"relationshipsSections":[{"title":"Conforms To","kind":"relationships","type":"conformsTo","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DriveProtocol","doc:\/\/GIO\/4GLib14PointerWrapperP"]}],"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"DriveRef","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"code":"GDrive","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is a container class for [iface"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Volume"},{"type":"text","text":"] objects that stem from"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the same piece of media. As such, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GDrive"},{"type":"text","text":" abstracts a drive with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(or without) removable media and provides operations for querying"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"whether media is available, determining whether media change is","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"automatically detected and ejecting the media.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If the "},{"code":"GDrive","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" reports that media isn’t automatically detected, one"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"can poll for media; typically one should not do this periodically"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"as a poll for media operation is potentially expensive and may"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"spin up the drive creating noise."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GDrive"},{"text":" supports starting and stopping drives with authentication","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"support for the former. This can be used to support a diverse set"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"of use cases including connecting\/disconnecting iSCSI devices,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"powering down external disk enclosures and starting\/stopping"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"multi-disk devices such as RAID devices. Note that the actual"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"semantics and side-effects of starting\/stopping a ","type":"text"},{"code":"GDrive","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" may vary","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"according to implementation. To choose the correct verbs in e.g. a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"file manager, use [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.Drive.get_start_stop_type"},{"text":"].","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"migrating-gnome-vfs.html","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" note that there is no"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"equivalent of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GDrive"},{"text":" in that API.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DriveRef","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" type acts as a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GDrive"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"It exposes methods that can operate on this data type through ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DriveProtocol","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" conformance."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DriveRef","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" only as an "},{"code":"unowned","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" reference to an existing "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GDrive"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Drive"},{"text":" (instead of ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DriveRef","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":") if you want to use Automatic Reference Counting for memory management of the underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GDrive"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"}]}],"name":"Note","type":"aside"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO"]]},"abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GDrive"},{"type":"text","text":" represents a piece of hardware connected to the machine."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It’s generally only created for removable hardware or hardware with","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"removable media. For example, an optical disc drive, or a USB flash drive."}],"sections":[],"references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/Drive":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Drive","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Drive","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/drive","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Drive","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GDrive"},{"type":"text","text":" represents a piece of hardware connected to the machine."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"It’s generally only created for removable hardware or hardware with","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"removable media. For example, an optical disc drive, or a USB flash drive."}],"title":"Drive"},"migrating-gnome-vfs.html":{"type":"link","identifier":"migrating-gnome-vfs.html","url":"migrating-gnome-vfs.html","title":"porting from GnomeVFS","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"porting from GnomeVFS","type":"text"}]},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/Volume":{"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/volume","title":"Volume","identifier":"doc:\/